# How To Work In This Devteam Workspace

This is a devteam-managed workspace. Do not treat this directory as a single
repository.

Workspace:

- Name: `{{WORKSPACE_NAME}}`
- Root: `{{WORKSPACE_ROOT}}`
- Config: `{{CONFIG_PATH}}`
- Default track: `{{DEFAULT_TRACK}}`

The `.devteam/config.yaml` file is the machine-readable source of truth. This
file is the agent onboarding entrypoint.

## First Action

When entering this workspace, inspect the dynamic devteam context before making
changes:

```bash
node "{{DEVTEAM_CLI}}" workspace context --root "$PWD" --for codex --text
```

Then choose or confirm a track:

```bash
node "{{DEVTEAM_CLI}}" track list --root "$PWD" --active-only --text
node "{{DEVTEAM_CLI}}" track context --root "$PWD" --set "<track>" --text
```

For a compact run/worktree/evidence view after selecting a track:

```bash
node "{{DEVTEAM_CLI}}" status --root "$PWD" --set "<track>"
```

If Codex/Claude skills are available, use `devteam-console` as the daily
workspace entrypoint and `devteam-status` for compact read-only summaries.

## Track Model

This workspace may contain multiple tracks. A session should bind itself to a
track instead of assuming a global active track.

Before editing code:

1. List or inspect available tracks.
2. Ask the user which track this session should work on unless the request
   clearly names one.
3. Start or select a run for that track.
4. Work only inside the worktrees belonging to that track.

Prefer session-local selection:

```bash
node "{{DEVTEAM_CLI}}" session start --root "$PWD" --set "<track>" --text
```

Do not use `track use` to mutate the workspace default when multiple sessions
may be active. Use `--set <track>` or a session-local `DEVTEAM_TRACK` instead.

